headers.subject: Fwd: US-Canada statement of privacy principles

html:
doesn't really apply to any website in particular, but might still be relevant.

"Timely and efficient information sharing between the United States and Canada is critical to the national security of both nations." - does that mean that if i'm using a Canadian-based websites, i can also be tracked by the FBI?

---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: ashok malhotra <ashok.malhotra@oracle.com>
Date: Wed, Jul 4, 2012 at 4:42 PM
Subject: Fwd: US-Canada statement of privacy principles
To: "www-tag@w3.org" <www-tag@w3.org>


From the privacy list

-------- Original Message --------
Subject: US-Canada statement of privacy principles
Resent-Date: Wed, 04 Jul 2012 13:31:24 +0000
Resent-From: public-privacy@w3.org
Date: Wed, 4 Jul 2012 15:30:54 +0200
From: Christine Runnegar <runnegar@isoc.org>
To: public-privacy@w3.org 


Last week, Canada and the United States released a joint Statement of Privacy Principles.

Here is a link to the press release:

http://www.dhs.gov/ynews/releases/20120628-us-and-canada-btb-statement-of-privacy-principles.shtm

and a link to the statement:

http://www.dhs.gov/xlibrary/assets/policy/beyond-the-border-action-plan-statement-of-privacy-principles.pdf

Cheers,
Christine
